      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPOTLIGHT (8) had been racing in great heart then went close again last time over 1800m at Globe Derby Park, finishing second and just a neck from the winner. Gets a soft run on the inside of the second line but may need luck at some point. Has the class to find the winners' list. TRANQUIL BILL (3) had to dig deep to salute at the most recent appearance over 2230m at Globe Derby Park, getting home by just 2 metres. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a comparable field so he can certainly win again. HAYOAK (7) didn't do a bad job when fourth over 2050m at Port Pirie last time out. Top-three credentials. CADENCE LANE (4) is worth some thought despite her last-start tenth over 1800m at Globe Derby Park on February 21. Capable of a lot more.",
